goals.question: What is the correlation between u and v?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of u vs v
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify if there is any relationship between the two variables. If there is a strong correlation, it can be used to predict one variable based on the other.

goals.question: What is the distribution of u?
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to understand the spread of the variable u. It can help to identify if the data is normally distributed or skewed.

goals.question: What is the distribution of v?
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to understand the spread of the variable v. It can help to identify if the data is normally distributed or skewed.

goals.question: What is the average value of u?
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify the median, quartiles, and outliers of the variable u. It can help to understand the central tendency of the data.

goals.question: What is the average value of v?
goals.rationale: This visualization helps to identify the median, quartiles, and outliers of the variable v. It can help to understand the central tendency of the data.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['u'], data['v'])
    plt.xlabel('u')
    plt.ylabel('v')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between u and v?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['u'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='u')
    plt.axvline(data['u'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['u'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of u?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("u")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot(data['u'])
    avg_u = data['u'].mean()
    ax.axhline(avg_u, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average: {avg_u:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the average value of u?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('u')
    plt.ylabel('Value')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
